About Celebrate Communities
Find your happy place and go there often!
Welcome! We hope you'll choose us as the next place you make your home. We take pride in building a strong sense of community for the residents that live with us. Your happiness in our communities, is the foundation and back-bone of our community environment.
Our Story
Our mission is to provide clean, safe, affordable, and enjoyable communities for our residents, and future residents.
We take pride in building a strong sense of community for the residents that live with us. Homeowners and renters in our communities are treated professionally and respectfully. We focus our time on helping building pride of ownership and we do this by focusing on the details.
​
Our Core Values
Resourceful
We find smart solutions, use what we have wisely, and always look for better ways to support our communities.
Integrity
We do what’s right, even when no one’s watching. We’re honest, dependable, and keep our promises to everyone.
Positive
We bring good energy, focus on what’s possible, and help create a friendly, can-do attitude across our communities.
Stewardship
We take care of what’s been trusted to us—our people, properties, and resources—with care, responsibility, and long-term thinking.
Find a Community
Find a Home
Contact Us
Why Celebrate Communities?
Let Our Residents Tell You!
Bonni Myszka
Resident
A quiet and peaceful place to live. The on-site managers keep the park looking neat, clean and cheerful. The pool is wonderful, and always sparkling clean. This retirement community is close to stores, and restaurants making it a great choice to call home.
Dwight Vonover
Resident
Kelley and Rick have been very helpful and have made me feel very at home in the park. Always responsive, and friendly.
Joseph Cappachione
Resident
Where do I begin? Our community is big, beautiful, and very clean. A great place to meet up with friends and find new ones as well. My favorites are the pool, and the laundry room, an added convenience for my life. Park residents are quiet and laid back, but never dull!
Peggy Henry
Resident
I have lived at Carter's Mobile Home Park for 8 years now, and we're a small community. Everyone looks out for each other. I have always felt safe here, and when the weather is right, we always have a place to socialize. It's nice to live here at Carters where I feel comfortable.
